this is just a backup repo of the scripts I use for building and deployment of Gentoo based Virtual Machines to my mini Virtualisation cluster. 


It's not very good and I don't recommend you using it, but it's good enought for me.

all deployment functionality is in deploy.sh scripts, it's designed for my specific KVM/Libvirt/Pacemaker/Ceph 

HOWTO:
	Build base image:
		./mksh.sh 
	backup base image:
		cp vm.img base.img
	use one of templates to customize base Image
	for example gh-docker (simple VM with docker daemon)
		USE_CACHED=base.img TEMPL=gh-docker ./mksh.sh

	To build and deply with one command use:
		DEPLOY=1 USE_CACHED=base.img TEMPL=gh-docker ./mksh.sh

to create new template recursively copy directory template
for ex.:
	cp -r template My_new_template_name
now you can customize it in file My_new_template_name/conf.sh
you can modify some properties variables written in CAPITAL LETTERS
to add packages in vm add them to TEMPLPKGS (simple space separated lis)
you can change VM image size with TEMPL_VM_IMG_SIZE_GB, it'll extend default base image if needed.
Write your custom.. stuff  inside SPEC_SETUP() function

If in doubt, check other existing templates





all VM images are created with btrfs filesystem with compression enabled
default image size is 3GB
Images don't have UEFI or BIOS booltloaders !!!!
They are designed for direct kernel boot via QEMU. 
	(Hypervisor boots kernel and initrd directly from host filesystem.)
These VMs normally run with my customized kernel config.
You can try using normal kernels if you know what you're doing.


SCRIPTS expect certain files which I didn't commint to this repo
ex. : public ssh key, nullmailer confguration files, libvirt ceph secred it, etc
You may have to profide them to for script to work


list of template:
	rt1 - router with nftables (nftables unfinished)
	gh-portage - gentoo poratage server: lighttpd binpkgs, local portage rsync, apt-cacher-ng basic config and mirrors, let's all HTTPS trafic through 
	gh-dns - dhcp, tftp and dns server for my lan. It also is responsible for netbooting (nfs booting) few machines real machines
	gh-distcc - basic vm just for running distccd (distributed c compilation)
	gh-factorio - factorio game server VM

